BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Speaker: Prof. Dr. Song Gao\, University of Wisconsin-Madison\, USA https://geography.wisc.edu/staff/gao-song/ Issues on Pre-Training and Applications of Urban Mobility Foundation Models This talk will discuss issues on the pre-training and downstream tasks of Urban Mobility Foundation Models (UMFMs). Specifically\, we need to consider multimodal mobility data and effective representation approaches\, ensure model interpretability\, and address geographical scale\, biases\, and location privacy issues. Prof. Dr. WenWen Li\, Arizona State University\, USA https://search.asu.edu/profile/1978357 GeoAI for Environmental Change: From Multimodality to Multitemporal Analysis This talk will introduce our work on analyzing environmental change using multimodal geospatial data. I will demonstrate how we move from analyzing single satellite images to a multimodal setting and then to multitemporal analysis\, enabling us to answer not only where environmental change is occurring but also when it began. I will also share applications of these GeoAI methods for near-real-time monitoring of Arctic environmental change and hazards as well as their impacts on local communities. Talk and discussion will be in English\nHost: Alexander Zipf\nVenue: IWR\, INF 205\, Room 5/104 (Conference Room)\nDuration: 1h
DTEND:20260623T121500Z
LOCATION:IWR\, INF 205\, Room 5/104 (Conference Room)
DTSTART:20260623T111500Z
SUMMARY:GIScience Colloquium
UID:e14cb3e2-7028-4987-b454-44ffc9c495a5@e14c.org
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Speaker: Dr. Liam Keegan As agentic coding tools like Claude Code and Codex CLI make generating code faster\, validating the correctness of this code becomes more important than ever. In this course you will learn how to apply test-driven development and software testing best practices in the context of agentic software development. By writing tests before the implementation\, our test suite not only verifies correctness\, but also defines a clear specification of what the code should and should not do\nHost: Scientific Software Center\nVenue: Mathematikon Bauteil A\, Im Neuenheimer Feld 205\, in the conference room 5/104 on the 5th floor\nLink: https://www.ssc.uni-heidelberg.de/en/agentic-test-driven-development\nDuration: 3h 30m
DTEND:20260723T110000Z
LOCATION:Mathematikon Bauteil A\, Im Neuenheimer Feld 205\, in the conference room 5/104 on the 5th floor
DTSTART:20260723T073000Z
SUMMARY:Compact course: Agentic Test-Driven Development
UID:af8f06b5-9409-45ff-9b5e-9d355dbcc955@af8f.org
URL:https://www.ssc.uni-heidelberg.de/en/agentic-test-driven-development
END:VEVENT
