BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Speaker: Rajesh Ranganath (NYU) Clinical risk scores are widely used in medical decision-making\, but evaluating alternative interventions and their timing remains challenging. Rajesh Ranganath will present*Competing Event Models (CEMs)*\, a generativeautoregressive framework for estimating intervention effects that addresses key limitations of standard transformer-based approaches. Rajeshis an associate professor at NYU's Courant Institute in Computer Science and the Center for Data Science. He is also affiliate faculty at the Department of Population Health at NYUMC. His research focuses on AI for healthcare\, generative models\, robustness and generalization\, and causal inference. Zoom participation is available for colleagues at other sites - but we strongly encourage local participants to join in person to take advantage of the opportunity for discussion and networking with the speaker. This time\, we also cannot promise optimal zoom quality: https://dkfz-de.zoom-x.de/meeting/register/6CNF36zFTDaisVMQczUHxA\nHost: AI in Life Seminar Series Team\nVenue: DKFZ TP3\, Ingrid Buchleiter Room B0.321\nLink: https://www.ai-life-delta.com/event/hd-ai-in-l-2/\nDuration: 1h
DTEND:20260619T100000Z
LOCATION:DKFZ TP3\, Ingrid Buchleiter Room B0.321
DTSTART:20260619T090000Z
SUMMARY:Clinical Risk Scores\, Causality & Competing Events with Autoregressive Transformers
UID:b9407543-e949-48bf-92a7-353aa7775849@b940.org
URL:https://www.ai-life-delta.com/event/hd-ai-in-l-2/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Speaker: Machine Learning in Astrophysical studies The workshop's theme is the application of machine learning to solve astrophysical problems. This event will be a one-day workshop and unconference\, where we will discuss and learn from each other about applying techniques to solve very similar problems in various contexts. We hope this workshop could lead to some new collaborations or initial joint studies. We will dedicate a significant amount of time to unconference sessions and informal discussions\nHost: Tobias Buck (IWR) Morgan Fouesneau (MPIA) Nikos Gianniotis (HITS) Guillaume Guiglion (ZAH/LSW\, MPIA) Ralf Klessen (ZAH/ITA) Annalisa Pillepich (MPIA) Kai Polsterer (HITS)\nVenue: Tagungszentrum Studio Villa Bosch Schloss-Wolfsbrunnenweg 33 69118 Heidelberg\nLink: https://mpi-astronomy.github.io/ml4astro2026/\nDuration: 9h 30m
DTEND:20260624T160000Z
LOCATION:Tagungszentrum Studio Villa Bosch Schloss-Wolfsbrunnenweg 33 69118 Heidelberg
DTSTART:20260624T063000Z
SUMMARY:ML4ASTRO
UID:68436abe-897f-4d9c-bf59-b5e87e677a3e@6843.org
